description.text:
Simple library for making masters for moulds from other openscad models.
This library will be maintained on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/beanz/mould-master-scad" >github</a>. To use the library just do:
<code >use &lt;mould-master.scad&gt;
master() {
  &lt;your-openscad-shape&gt;
}</code>
Enjoy!
Thanks to my youngest son for encouraging me to make this.
Thanks to Richard Horne (RichRap) for his <a rel="nofollow" href="http://richrap.blogspot.co.uk/2016/02/using-3d-printing-for-taste-of.html" >fabulous Trio project</a> write up that I was able to find the perfect silicone that is soft<br />
enough to get the chocolates out in one piece.
Thanks DWR Plastics for the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.dwrplastics.com/product-information/538a068b9ed12/RTV-Addition-Platinum-Cure-Food-Skin-SafeSilicone-Mould-Making-Rubber-1kg-kit" >perfect silicone</a>.
